🚀 Pulse — Social Media Dashboard

A modern, responsive Social Media Analytics Dashboard built using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. This project provides an interactive interface to monitor social media performance, visualize engagement metrics, and manage content efficiently.

⸻

📌 Project Overview

Pulse Dashboard is designed for content creators and social media managers to:
	•	Track followers and engagement
	•	Analyze performance across platforms
	•	Monitor post performance
	•	Visualize data using charts
	•	Simulate API integrations for real-world usage

⚠️ Note: This project currently uses mock data to simulate real API responses.

⸻

✨ Features

📊 Dashboard Overview
	•	Displays key metrics:
	•	Followers count
	•	Engagement rate
	•	Growth percentage
	•	Average likes per post
	•	Interactive follower growth chart
	•	Platform traffic distribution (Donut chart)

⸻

📈 Analytics Section
	•	Total posts, average likes, and comments
	•	Monthly engagement trends (Line chart)
	•	Engagement split (Likes vs Comments)
	•	Platform performance comparison (Bar chart)

⸻

📝 Posts Management
	•	Top performing posts table (sorted by likes)
	•	Engagement percentage visualization
	•	Performance categorization (High / Medium / Low)
	•	Scheduled posts display with status:
	•	Scheduled
	•	Draft
	•	Review

⸻

⚙️ Settings
	•	Toggle Dark / Light Mode
	•	Theme preference saved using localStorage
	•	Profile and notification placeholders

⸻

🔌 API Integration (Simulated)
	•	Connect to platforms like:
	•	Instagram
	•	Twitter
	•	YouTube
	•	Token-based connection UI
	•	Simulated real-time data fetching
	•	Status indicators (Connected / Disconnected)

⸻

🛠️ Technologies Used
	•	HTML5 — Structure
	•	CSS3 — Styling and responsive design
	•	JavaScript (Vanilla) — Logic and interactivity
	•	Chart.js — Data visualization
	•	LocalStorage — Theme persistence

⸻

📂 Project Structure
Pulse-Dashboard/
│
├── index.html      # Main UI structure
├── style.css       # Styling and themes
├── script.js       # Functionality and logic
└── README.md       # Project documentation

